{"word":"H3948 - לֶקַח - leqach - leh'-kakh - Doctrine","slug":"H3948","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">לֶקַח</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>leqach"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>leh'-kakh"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Doctrine"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05DC;&#x05E7;&#x05D7; - leqach</b> - <i>leh'-kakh</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/H3947\">H3947</a>; properly something <i>received</i>, that is, (mentally) <i>instruction</i> (whether on the part of the teacher or hearer); also (in an active and sinister sense) <i>inveiglement: - </i>doctrine, learning, fair speech."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H3947\">H3947</a>, <a href=\"#/H3949\">H3949</a>, <a href=\"#/H4455\">H4455</a>, <a href=\"#/H4457\">H4457</a>, <a href=\"#/H4727\">H4727</a>, <a href=\"#/H4728\">H4728</a>"}]}